  "doc_id": "1047",
  "text": "1. Annotate the genome of the target organism and highlight its metabolic functions. The Z. parabailii genes were automatically obtained with an improved version of the Yeast Genome Annotation Pipeline based on homology and synteny information from 20 different yeast species from the Saccharomycetaceae family [CITATION_1] . These gene predictions were curated using Illumina RNAseq data using the Trinity / Pasa pipeline followed by manual inspection [CITATION_2] . Afterwards, Enzyme Commission (EC) numbers were obtained using Blast2GO as previously reported [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
